OL,6,FShe also urged the public to be extra
OL,7,Fvigilant when crossing a green man
OL,8,Fbecause "more people will die at the
OL,9,Fhands of the police because they can
OL,10,Fjust go through a red light, kill a
OL,11,Fpedestrian when it's their right of
OL,12,Fway."
OL,14,FDuring the trial, the court heard PC
OL,15,FHarrison - an experienced rider with
OL,16,Fthe Met's specialist escort group -
OL,17,Fwas travelling between 44mph and 58mph
OL,18,Fin a 30mph zone as he approached the
OL,19,Fcontrolled crossing, which was red for
OL,20,Ftraffic at the time.
